      },
      "date": "2017-05-03 13:51:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nIs this still needed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "ef79dec78fbd67ccb8d108cec27a47d4d539ec99",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-05 10:58:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThere is still a need to better register traps, in test_24d more than the other tests (as we saw that when 24d does not properly clean itself up, it may induce many other unrelated failures).\n\nThere are other issues as well:\n * most tests register traps after the setup action was performed, that means that if a test fails between the setup and the trap registration (thourgh <Ctrl-c> for example), the test will not clean up properly, and there may be side effects on the next test run.\n * test_12q has pretty much the same problems as test_24d ;\n * the current fix of \"calling the previous trap handler from the current trap handler\" is tedious and error prone ;\n * trap handler are explicitely (and unnecessarily) called at the end of tests\n\nThe current patch is far from correcting all these issues, and since there is no rush to fixing it now, I will work on a better fix.\n\nIn a nutshell, changes are needed, it will take some time but this is not a blocking issue anymore.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "3290c8a5198eae63cc96597831c0610c732a4495",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-07 08:43:06.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nAbandonned in favor of https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/29653/",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    }
