          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Quentin Bouget",
          "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
          "date": "2017-04-18 14:43:28.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Quentin Bouget",
          "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
          "date": "2017-04-26 08:25:37.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-9306 tests: sanity-hsm, register traps in a better order",
        "message": "LU-9306 tests: sanity-hsm, register traps in a better order\n\nTraps are used in tests to define actions to perform on cleanup.\nThe copytool_setup() functions registers its own trap in order to\nensure any copytool that is launched gets killed at some point.\n\nUnfortunately there is no built-in way to register several traps.\nTherefore when test_24d calls copytool_setup() it overwrites\ncleanup_test_24d.\n\nThis patch is a temporary fix to this issue in sanity-hsm.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-hsm,sanity-hsm,sanity-hsm\nSigned-off-by: Quentin Bouget <quentin.bouget@cea.fr>\nChange-Id: I6e68117d8dd4ba5483aa47b3ac326f2669912450\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
